                            <comment id="211246" author="ofaaland" created="Mon, 16 Oct 2017 21:42:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Jinshan, thank you.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would like all three patches.&#160; Re: 28924, I want to preserve the ability of the other sites to upgrade to ZFS 0.7.0 and then roll back if they find they need to, even though that is unlikely.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="211004" author="jay" created="Fri, 13 Oct 2017 00:29:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve pushed the patch to &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/29596&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/29596&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another patch is probably needed: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/28345&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/28345&lt;/a&gt;, if you&apos;re going to iterate quote info from OI object. However, I don&apos;t think you should need patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/28924&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/28924&lt;/a&gt;. Less patch means less problem. Please let me know if you want any or both of them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="210896" author="pjones" created="Wed, 11 Oct 2017 21:19:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bob&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please assist with this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="210835" author="ofaaland" created="Wed, 11 Oct 2017 17:22:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To quantify this, we see 500-1000 such messages per month on the servers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="210832" author="ofaaland" created="Wed, 11 Oct 2017 17:08:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please backport the following to allow Lustre 2.8 to use ZFS&apos; native object accounting:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2435&quot; title=&quot;inode accounting in osd-zfs is racy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2435&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2435&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/15294/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/15294/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9960&quot; title=&quot;Rolling downgrade master to 2.10 - unable to import zpools&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9960&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9960&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/28924/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/28924/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The messages could just be changed from CERROR to CDEBUG, but the patches are small.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
